<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLAUDE ARPELS, 79; PRESIDENT OF PARIS-BASED JEWELRY CHAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Claude Arpels, 79, president of Van Cleef and Arpels who opened the Paris-based 
jewelry chain's Beverly Hills salon. 
</P>
<P>
He and his two brothers inherited and operated the prestigious business founded 
by their parents and in-laws. He spent most of his career in the U.S. 
operation, opening the New York store on 5th Avenue in 1939, a shop in Palm 
Beach, Fla., in 1940, and the Beverly Hills store on Rodeo Drive in 1969. In 
Paris on Monday of unknown causes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
