response of correcting bad behavior with bad law. It won't solve our problems. 
Ultimately, it will exacerbate them by forcing exorbitant future costs on 
society and stymie targeted efforts to deal intelligently with specific 
problems. Policy often has undiscovered consequences. Big Green would be a Big 
Mistake. 
</P>
<P>
KIP DELLINGER, Los Angeles 
