<P>
THERE'S LITTLE DEFENSE AGAINST THE USC BAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ears and brain can take only so much and I hope I never hear the USC band 
again. 
</P>
<P>
Having been totally annoyed in the past, I decided at Saturday's USC-Stanford 
game to try to count the number of times the Trojan Band played all or part of 
its fanfare (called "Conquest," I think). The total I got was 46 and I probably 
missed a few. 
</P>
<P>
What the USC band director forgets (or ignores) is that any mature brain begins 
to filter out the constant music. And finally it is totally tuned out or the 
trapped listener is driven wild. 
</P>
<P>
HARRY PRESS 
