when Bobby Savannah teamed with Rockey Tribble on a 50-yard pass play with 4:58 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
South Gate is 3-2 and 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
Fairfax 28, Los Angeles 14 -- Milo Bynum returned a blocked field-goal attempt 
99 yards in the first quarter to help Lions (3-0, 5-0) remain unbeaten in a 
Coastal Conference game at Fairfax. 
</P>
<P>
Senior tailback Mario Mattison, who led Fairfax with 96 yards rushing and a 
touchdown in 10 carries, blocked the kick returned by Bynum. 
</P>
<P>
Fairfax is 1-1, 2-3. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham 21, Grant 13 -- Darrel Moore scored twice and gained 95 yards in 22 
carries for the Braves in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game at Grant. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham quarterback Vince Lampkin rushed for 77 yards and a touchdown, but 
left the game in the second quarter with a sprained left ankle. His 
replacement, Noah Kirshbaum, completed five of 13 passes for 62 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Grant (3-3, 1-2) scored two touchdowns in the third quarter, but Eddy Moreno's 
conversion kick after the second touchdown was wide, enabling the Braves to 
maintain a 14-13 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Moore scored on another two-yard plunge 38 seconds into the fourth quarter, and 
Birmingham (4-1, 2-0) held on for the win. 
</P>
<P>
Lincoln 49, Verdugo Hills 0 -- Brothers Gaspar and Marcelo Ortega combined for 
five touchdowns and Lincoln's defense forced five turnovers in a Northern 
Conference game at Verdugo Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Senior quarterback Gaspar Ortega completed 11 of 20 passes for 189 yards and 
four touchdowns, including two 18-yard pass plays to his brother. Gaspar 
Ortega's other touchdown pass plays covered 50 and four yards. Gaspar also 
kicked five extra points. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to his two touchdown receptions, Marcelo Ortega, scored on a 
10-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Lincoln tailback Roland Peters led all rushers with 142 yards and a touchdown 
in 10 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Lincoln is 2-1 and 4-1-1. Verdugo Hills is 0-3 and 0-6. 
</P>
