<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BELMONT COMES BACK TO BEAT EAGLE ROCK, 16-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK STRODER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Belmont High spotted Eagle Rock a 7-0 lead but came back to score a 16-7 
victory over the Eagles in a City Section Northern Conference game at Eagle 
Rock Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The key play for Belmont came with one minute remaining in the second quarter 
when halfback Edgar Moreno completed a 50-yard option pass to David Panameno, 
which set up John Evans' four-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
"We practice that play every day, but this is the first time we've used it," 
Belmont Coach Rob Levy said after his team improved to 2-1 in conference play 
and 4-1 overall. "We had to try it, nothing else was working." 
</P>
<P>
Belmont took a 10-7 lead after Juan Ramos kicked a 27-yard field goal three 
minutes into the third quarter and, eight minutes later, the Centenials mounted 
10-play, 66-yard scoring drive. The touchdown came on a 21-yard pass from 
Conteraras to Moreno. 
</P>
<P>
Belmont's defense dominated the second half, allowing Eagle Rock only 10 yards 
in net offense, Eagle quarterback Eddy Espinoza was sacked five times for 47 
yards in losses. MARK STRODER 
</P>
