ARIZONA; 
</P>
<P>
CONVICTED NAVAJO TO BE KEPT OFF BALLOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Navajo Indian tribal council voted to keep suspended tribal Chairman Peter 
MacDonald off the ballot for the tribe's forthcoming presidential election in 
Window Rock, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
The council voted 71 to 11 against MacDonald and postponed the Nov. 6 election 
for 60 days. MacDonald has been found guilty in tribal District Court of 41 
counts of bribery, theft by extortion and breaking tribal ethics laws. 
Businessmen testified that they had paid thousands of dollars in kickbacks in 
exchange for business contracts on the reservation. 
