<HEADLINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA STOPS CENTURY, 21-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARGIE LUCK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryan McEvoy passed for 212 yards Friday night as Costa Mesa High School easily 
defeated Pacific Coast League rival Century, 21-6, at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, the Centurions were on their own 29 when quarterback Rick 
Odoardi (five of nine for 177 yards) was intercepted by David Phillips. 
</P>
<P>
McEvoy pulled off a quarterback sneak for 17 yards, which set up Jermaine 
Jackson's 12-yard run into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
In the third quarter, with the Centurions leading, 6-0, Jackson (12 carries, 68 
yards) scored again, running 11 yards. A pass from McEvoy to Quoc Pham (eight 
receptions, 64 yards) gave the Centurions a two-point conversion. 
</P>
<P>
Odoardi completed five of nine passes for 177 yards and threw two 
interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Both teams are 3-4, 1-1 in league play. MARGIE LUCK 
</P>
</TEXT>
