<P>
SANTA MARIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Josh Ireland scored two touchdowns and rushed for 89 yards to lead Santa 
Margarita High School to a 20-12 victory over Santa Maria in a nonleague game 
at Santa Maria Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Turnovers led to two of Santa Margarita's scores. Steve Feeney's interception 
and eight-yard return put Santa Margarita at the Santa Maria 15, and Ireland 
scored five plays later from the two to give Santa Margarita (7-0) a 14-6 
halftime lead. 
