<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAURICE WILSON'S 75-YARD RUN SAVES BOLSA GRANDE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bolsa Grande Coach Bill Holst said it was homecoming that did it for the 
Matadors, inspiring them to their second Garden Grove league victory, 13-10, 
over Garden Grove High School. 
</P>
<P>
"We've gone nuts all week long," he said. 
</P>
<P>
"Our kids came ready to play. Our defense was superb. They watched (Garden 
Grove) films all week, so they knew what to expect." 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande might not have expected to win after fumbling five times -- 
although it recovered three of them -- and throwing two interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Still, the Matadors won, thanks to Maurice Wilson's game-winning, 75-yard 
touchdown run with 9:36 left. The extra-point attempt failed, but Bolsa Grande 
(3-4, 2-2) held off Garden Grove (3-4, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande fell behind, 7-0, in the first quarter after Simon Fuentes hit 
Jason Baca with a 35-yard touchdown pass. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors tied the score in the third quarter, when quarterback Bryan 
Taylor's 44-yard run set up a three-yard touchdown run by Marcus Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove's Adrian Ioja missed a 30-yard field goal attempt, but seemed to 
redeem himself with a 26-yard kick with 10:11 left in the game before Maurice 
Wilson's run turned the lead into a loss. HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
