<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARINA GETS TO KARLINER, BEATS OCEAN VIEW, 17-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Randy Karliner played well, but Ocean View High's offensive line couldn't 
penetrate a strong Marina defense in the Seahawks' 17-7 loss Friday at 
Westminster High School. 
</P>
<P>
Karliner, sacked six times and intercepted once for a Marina touchdown, 
completed 12 of 28 passes for 193 yards for Ocean View (4-2-1, 2-1 in league 
play). 
</P>
<P>
He also completed a 34-yard touchdown pass to Jeff Bush in the final 1 minute 
41 seconds of the game and carried 15 times for 73 of Ocean View's 155 yards 
rushing. 
</P>
<P>
Marina's Ingmar Northcott sacked Karliner three times unassisted, and assisted 
on two more. Marina (5-2-1, 2-1), which only executed 14 plays in the first 
half, took its first possession at its 20 after Ocean View's Ron Lightner 
missed a 38-yard field goal with 6:24 left in the first quarter. Shawn Fulford, 
who rushed for 102 of Marina's 164 yards, had a 45-yard run during this 
nine-play drive. He scored from the one with 2:39 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
In the fourth quarter, Dan Armstrong's 39-yard field goal gave Marina a 10-0 
lead with 8:16 to play. Three plays after the ensuing kick, Chad Henderson 
picked off Karliner's pass at the Ocean View 23 and ran it into the end zone in 
the final 7:35. BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
