<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY JUST CAN'T WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE AGUL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dominguez High School handed Fountain Valley its seventh consecutive loss, 
44-30, Friday in a nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley (0-7), playing before a homecoming crowd of 3,000, led, 20-16, 
at halftime, but 28 second-half points by Dominguez (5-2) put the game away. 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez scored first on a 13-yard run by James Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
With seconds left in the quarter, Fountain Valley's Mike Pecen intercepted a 
pass at the Dominguez 35 and ran it back for a tying touchdown. Fountain 
Valley's Brian Williams scored the game's next touchdown on a 41-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez halfback Lavelle Townsend took the ensuing kickoff 99 yards for a 
touchdown, but the point-after attempt failed. Dominguez took a 16-14 lead on a 
field goal, but with 3:29 left in the half, Fountain Valley's Marcos Diaz 
caught a 19-yard pass for a touchdown and a 20-16 halftime lead. VINCE AGUL 
</P>
</TEXT>
