<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH HANDS TITANS ANOTHER VOLLEYBALL LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Antoinnette White had 16 kills to lead Cal State Long Beach to a 15-9, 15-1, 
15-5 victory over Cal State Fullerton in Big West Conference women's volleyball 
Friday at Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Defending NCAA champion Long Beach (15-6, 5-4 in conference) is ranked 13 in 
the nation. The Titans are 6-21, 2-8. 
</P>
<P>
In Golden State Athletic Conference volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 3, Fresno Pacific 1 -- Krista Hoover had 17 kills 
in leading host Southern California College (16-17, 5-4) to an upset of Fresno 
Pacific (21-13, 5-4), the sixth-ranked team in the NAIA. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 1, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Kevin Smith scored the goal for Irvine 
(5-4-1, 1-4-1) in its victory over Fullerton (5-4-3, 3-3-1). 
</P>
