<P>
GABLE BREAKS MONROE WITH 330-YARD EFFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leon Gable rushed for 330 yards in 39 carries and scored all four of his team's 
touchdowns to lead North Hollywood High to a 31-20 victory over Monroe in a 
Valley Pac-8 Conference game Friday night at Monroe. 
</P>
<P>
Gable, who ran for 327 yards two weeks ago against Van Nuys, scored on runs of 
32, one, 13 and 18 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Gable gave North Hollywood (3-2, 2-1) a 15-7 lead with his first two 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe (0-4-1, 0-3) cut North Hollywood's lead to 15-14 in the second quarter 
when running back Kijana Foster ran 27 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Gable scored two more touchdowns in the third quarter to put North Hollywood 
comfortably ahead. Gable carried 10 times on a 12-play, 80-yard drive on the 
Huskies' first possession of the second half and scored from 13 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe quarterback Ramy Atoun completed five of 11 passes for 157 yards. TODD 
JACOBSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
