<P>
GOLDEN WEST READIES FOR 25TH ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN PENNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West College officials plan to celebrate the school's 25th anniversary 
next year in a big way, and a committee has been named to prepare gala events. 
</P>
<P>
Faculty and staff members, alumni, students and community representatives on 
the panel are planning eight months of festivities that will begin in 
September, 1991, committee chairman John Wordes said. 
</P>
<P>
The silver anniversary will be different than the college's 1986-87 celebration 
of its 20th year, said Wordes, who has been on the faculty since the college 
opened in September, 1966. 
</P>
<P>
Whereas the 20-year anniversary focused upon the achievements of faculty and 
alumni, next year's celebration will include the surrounding community, he 
said.JOHN PENNER 
