<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Air Regulator Recall: A diving equipment manufacturer based in Santa Ana 
announced Friday that it has voluntarily recalled all of its air regulators 
because they may allow too much air to flow into divers' lungs. 
</P>
<P>
The company, U.S. Divers, said that a functional problem with the high pressure 
seats of the first stage of the regulators may allow an uncontrolled flow of 
air to its second stage. "If this occurs during a dive, use of the product 
could be hazardous," the company said. U.S. Divers said the recall affects all 
regulators that were purchased or serviced since Aug. 15. The company did not 
indicate whether any injuries have resulted because of the problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
