<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: INTERNATIONAL TRADE; 
</P>
<P>
HEALTHTRADE SIGNS DEAL: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Cristina Lee / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HealthTrade International Inc., a Mission Viejo trading company specializing in 
medical and health care equipment, said it has recently signed an agreement to 
provide artificial lenses to several hospitals in Southern China. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Bart S. Chapman, president of HealthTrade, said the value of the contract 
is small but may open the door to future sales in China. He said Chinese 
officials have already indicated that they plan to order more artificial lenses 
next year. 
</P>
<P>
The artificial lenses will be used by people suffering from cataracts. 
</P>
<P>
Chapman said his company is currently negotiating with other Chinese hospitals 
to supply them with advanced computerized medical equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
