<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIAM JOHN MCLAUGHLIN JR.; RETIRED POLICE OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William John McLaughlin Jr., a retired Los Angeles police officer, has died in 
a Woodland Hills hospital. He was 64. 
</P>
<P>
A longtime Van Nuys resident, McLaughlin died Oct. 12 of cancer, said his wife, 
Kathleen McLaughlin. 
</P>
<P>
Born Oct. 15, 1925, in Los Angeles, McLaughlin graduated from Van Nuys High 
School in 1943 and served in the Navy during World War II. He joined the Los 
Angeles Police Department in 1948. He worked patrol in various divisions, 
including Van Nuys and West Valley, and retired in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife of 40 years; sons David McLaughlin of Sunland and 
William John McLaughlin III of Redwood City, Calif.; daughter Cynthia Wooten of 
Eugene, Ore.; sister Jean Lind of Concord, Calif.; and two granddaughters. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service is scheduled for 11 a.m. today at Granada Hills Church of 
Religious Science, 17622 Chatsworth St., where he was a member. The Neptune 
Society in Burbank is handling the arrangements. Donations can be made to a 
memorial fund in McLaughlin's name at the church. 
</P>
</TEXT>
